{{Quote|To be young, gifted, and black though, right?|Riri Williams to [[Shuri]]|Black Panther: Wakanda Forever}}
'''Riri Williams''' is a former [[MIT]] student and a gifted inventor, who created various cutting-edge designs, such as her own '''Ironheart''' [[Ironheart Armor: Mark I|armor]], based on [[Iron Man]]'s suits. As one of her [[Vibranium Detector|projects]] was used by the [[CIA]] to find [[vibranium]] outside [[Wakanda]], Williams found herself threatened by [[Namor]], since her invention put [[Talokan]] in danger of being exposed to the surface world. Targeted by both [[Talokanil]] and the [[United States]] Government, Williams was approached by [[Shuri]] and the Wakandans, which later escalated into a [[Talokanil-Wakandan War|war]] between Wakanda and Talokan. Ironheart helped the Wakandans in the [[Ambush on the Talokanil|final battle]], using a new [[Ironheart Armor: Mark II|armor]], made with Wakandan technology, and returned to the U.S. after the conflict.

Williams continued her side hustle to get enough money to construct the armor of her dreams, which eventually resulted in her getting expelled from MIT and returning to [[Chicago]]. Williams did not abandon her dream and continued working on a suit, while being approached by [[Hood]], who promised her money for working for his [[Hood's Gang|gang]]. Despite warnings from [[N.A.T.A.L.I.E.]], an [[Artificial Intelligence|A.I.]] accidentally created in the image of her late best friend [[Natalie Washington]], Williams continued working for Hood, but soon realized that she and her loved ones were in danger. Being confronted by the threats of [[magic]], Ironheart managed to overcome her deep-seated fear and defeated Hood, before being approached by [[Mephisto]], who resurrected Washington for her as a part of their deal.

==Biography==
===Early Life===
====Childhood Prodigy====
{{Quote|My stepfather was an auto mechanic. He wanted to build airplanes but. He'd give me these tools and let me just work it out.|Riri Williams|Black Panther: Wakanda Forever}}
Riri Williams was born to [[Ronnie Williams]] in [[2005]], with her father having passed away.{{Ref|IH101}} She grew up in [[Chicago]]{{Ref|BPWF}} and started building machines at the age of three.{{Ref|MSCEUE}} She learned a lot about mechanics from [[Gary Williams|Gary]], her stepfather who wanted to build airplanes. She often took his tools and just fidget with his airplanes.{{Ref|BPWF}} Together, she and her dad worked on a [[Gary Williams' Car|Plymouth Barracuda]]. One day at the [[Gary's Auto Repair|auto shop]], Gary kissed her on the forehead as she was on the ground. She graduated ninth grade at the age of eleven. Riri was constantly making the news headlines, and constantly had articles written in the {{WPS|Chicago Tribune}} about her. At the age of twelve, she became the youngest ever to win at the Chicago Science Fair with a [[Robo-Dog]], and had an article written by the [[Chicago Central City Press]] about her victory. As a teenager, she attended [[South Shore International College Preparatory High School]], and, due to her genius mind, graduated in [[2020]], and started college at the age of fifteen.{{Ref|IH101}}

====Losing Gary and Natalie====
''To be added.''{{Ref|IH101}}

===College Career===
====Attending MIT====
{{Quote|I'm here about the [[Vibranium Detector]] you built for the [[CIA]]."<br>"I ain't build no detector for no CIA. I made that for my metallurgy class.|[[Shuri]] and Riri Williams|Black Panther: Wakanda Forever}}
Fresh out of high school, Williams was accepted into and attended [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]], where she settled into her single dorm and soon ran a business. She completed other students' homework for money, with the money being electronically transferred to her. Williams later became infatuated with creating her own [[Iron Man]]-style armor and worked on it intermittently in her own [[Riri Williams' Garage|garage]]. She also set up a very sophisticated computer password that she accidentally locked herself out of, which took her her a semester to regain access. At the age of nineteen, Williams designed a [[Vibranium Detector]], which she created using scraps of junk, after her professor believed that she would never be able to build it.{{Ref|BPWF}}

====Meeting Shuri and Okoye====
[[File:Riri meets Shuri.png|{{AltFloat}}|Williams is shocked to meet Princess [[Shuri]]]]
{{Quote|You're Princess Shuri! What the hell are you doing [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology|here]]? Oh, shit, am I going to be recruited?"<br>"No.|Riri Williams and [[Shuri]]|Black Panther: Wakanda Forever}}
In [[2025|May 2025]], Williams approached her friend, who did not pay her for the homework she had done for him. She swiftly took his phone and transferred the money herself. She then went back to her dorm where she met Princess [[Shuri]] from [[Wakanda]], who she instantly recognized. Williams wondered if she was being recruited, but Shuri revealed that she was there in regard to the [[Vibranium Detector]]. 
[[File:Riri with heater.png|{{AltFloat}}|Williams learns about the danger she is in]]
The two discussed the machine until Williams wondered if she had upset the Wakandans, so Shuri clarified it was not just them and that Williams was no longer safe and had to leave with her immediately. Williams became worried and tried to escape through the bathroom, but was blocked by [[Okoye]], who had been hiding there the whole time. Williams demanded they leave her dorm and threw a speaker at Okoye, but she sliced it in half. Shuri went to leave, informing Williams that she would have to deal with [[Namor]] alone, so Williams decided to go with them.{{Ref|BPWF}}

===[[Talokanil-Wakandan War]]===
====[[Chase of Riri Williams|Chased by the FBI]]====
[[File:Williams'Garage.png|{{AltFloat}}|Riri brings [[Shuri]] and [[Okoye]] to her [[Riri Williams' Garage|garage]]]]
{{Quote|I must be dumb as hell. Real dumb thinking that the [[Shuri|Princess]] of [[Wakanda]] is gonna show up at my doorstep and then shit about to pop off. I think that I'm actually gonna take my chances with this [[Namor|merman]] because at least he never brought the [[FBI]] to my [[Riri Williams' Garage|garage]]!|Riri Williams to [[Okoye]]|Black Panther: Wakanda Forever}}
Williams brought [[Okoye]] and [[Shuri]] to her [[Riri Williams' Garage|garage]], where she told them not to touch anything. Williams collected her computer, explaining that it had her life's work on it. [[Griot]] notified them that the [[FBI]] had arrived and were surrounding the garage, demanding Williams to step out.
[[File:She got an Iron Man suit!.png|{{AltFloat}}|Williams suits up to escape from the [[FBI]]]]
Williams became annoyed that the FBI had been led to her garage, putting all her work at risk, so she began burning her designs. Shuri and Okoye discussed their next course of actions, so Williams revealed her [[Ironheart Armor: Mark I|suit]], stating she would be using it to escape. Shuri gave Williams a wireless transmitter so they could communicate before entering Williams' [[Gary Williams|stepfather]]'s car with Okoye. Williams suited up, and when the FBI breached the garage, she fired a shot at them before flying outside through an opening in the roof.
[[File:Riri Pulled Down.png|{{AltFloat}}|Williams is knocked out by the [[Talokanil]]]]
Griot noted that there was a surveillance drone tracking them, so Williams went to destroy it, working out the calculations so that it would crash into the police blocking the bridge. Williams successfully shot the drone out of the sky, however, she passed out from lack of oxygen and began plummeting towards the water. Williams regained consciousness before crashing and regrouped with Shuri and Okoye at the bridge. But, Williams was knocked out by the [[Talokanil]], who took her and Shuri to [[Talokan]].{{Ref|BPWF}}

====[[Escape from Namor's Cenote]]====
[[File:Riri Williams & Nakia.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Williams is rescued from [[Namor]] by [[Nakia]]]]
{{Quote|The [[T'Challa|Black Panther]] is gone."<br>"So y'all stop having [[:Category:Black Panthers|Black Panthers]] when I get kidnapped?|[[Shuri]] and Riri Williams|Black Panther: Wakanda Forever}}
Williams woke up in a [[Namor's Cenote|cave]] and panicked, so [[Shuri]] tried to calm her down. Williams asked if a [[:Category:Black Panthers|Black Panther]] would be sent to rescue them, but Shuri informed her that there were no more Black Panthers. [[Namora]] entered and told Shuri to come with her, causing Williams to worry about being left alone. When Shuri returned, she revealed to Williams that Namor intended to go to war with the surface and he wanted [[Wakanda]] to fight with him. They were then rescued by [[Nakia]], who arrived and shot the two guards, allowing them to escape back to the surface, where they were picked up by a [[Royal Talon Fighter]].{{Ref|BPWF}}

====[[Attack on Birnin Zana]]====
[[File:Ramonda and Riri.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Riri is protected by [[Ramonda]] from [[Namor]]]]
{{Quote|Go, child."<br>"Wait, what? And leave you here?|[[Ramonda]] and Riri Williams|Black Panther: Wakanda Forever}}
Williams was brought to [[Wakanda]], where she met Queen [[Ramonda]] and was shown to the [[Citadel]]. Suddenly, Wakanda fell under attack by the [[Talokanil]], so Williams assisted Ramonda in using the high-tech windows to help civilians. They were confronted by [[Namor]], who used a [[Hydrobomb]] to attack them, flooding the room. Williams was saved from drowning by Ramonda, and was quickly resuscitated, only to discover that the Queen had died saving her.{{Ref|BPWF}}

====Helping Shuri====
[[File:Riri Williams (Black Panther- Wakanda Forever).jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Williams works on building a trap for [[Namor]]]]
{{Quote|Your [[Ramonda|mother]] protected me like I was one of her own. The least that I could do is try to return the favor.|Riri Williams to [[Shuri]]|Black Panther: Wakanda Forever}}
Following the funeral, Williams approached [[Shuri]] and told her that [[Ramonda]]'s sacrifice made her feel the need to help them stop [[Namor]]. Shuri stated they needed to weaken Namor, and that she would become the next Black Panther. Williams and Shuri discussed Namor's physiology and figured out that heat would weaken him, so Shuri placed Williams in charge of converting the [[Royal Talon Fighter]] into a trap for him.
[[File:Riri Williams creating Ironheart Armor.png|{{AltFloat}}|Williams builds herself a new [[Ironheart Armor: Mark II|suit of armor]]]]
As Williams worked on the trap, she also built herself new [[Ironheart Armor: Mark II|armor]], which Shuri consulted on. During the process, Williams and Shuri bonded over how they were introduced to building things. When Shuri successfully recreated the [[Heart-Shaped Herb]], Williams and [[Nakia]] helped her take it, with Williams worried about the dangers of the ritual. When Shuri awoke, they discovered Shuri's newfound strength, making Williams express her desire to also take the Herb.{{Ref|BPWF}}

====[[Ambush on the Talokanil]]====
[[File:Ironheart vs. Namor.png|{{AltFloat}}|Williams fires upon an approaching [[Namor]]]]
{{Quote|For the [[Ramonda|Queen]].|Riri Williams|Black Panther: Wakanda Forever}}
[[Black Panther]] led the [[Wakanda]]ns to ambush the [[Talokanil]] on the ''[[Sea Leopard]]''. Creating another [[Vibranium Detector]], Williams used it to lure the Talokanil. When [[Namor]] appeared, Williams attacked him, but he soon overwhelmed her, so she requested assistance from [[Griot]]. The [[Royal Talon Fighter]] was flown in and captured Namor after Williams disoriented him with a blast.
[[File:Ironheart defeats Namora.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Williams fights against and defeats [[Namora]]]]
Williams informed the others of Namor's capture and went to help the rest of the Wakandans fight off the Talokanil. When Williams went underwater, [[Namora]] grabbed onto the suit and began attacking it, so Williams resurfaced and attempted to shake her off. Williams managed to get Namora in front of her, allowing her to blast her enemy with a chest beam. Williams regrouped with the rest of the Wakandans, but were soon outnumbered and surrounded. Fortunately, Black Panther returned with Namor and they announced their truce, ending the war between them.{{Ref|BPWF}}

====Leaving Wakanda====
[[File:Black Panther II Trailer (26).png|{{AltFloat}}|Riri talks to [[Shuri]] before leaving [[Wakanda]]]]
{{Quote|Your [[Ironheart Armor: Mark II|suit]]. It's a great design, but can't let you leave with it."<br>"It's all good. Figured the least I could do is help [[Wakanda]] clean up my mess.|[[Shuri]] and Riri Williams|Black Panther: Wakanda Forever}}
No longer in danger, Williams went back to [[Wakanda]] and prepared to return home. [[Shuri]] spoke with Williams before she left, telling her that she would not be allowed to leave with her new [[Ironheart Armor: Mark II|armor]], which Williams understood. Shuri then revealed that she had repaired Williams' [[Gary Williams|stepfather]]'s car, which would be transported back to [[Boston]] with her. Williams invited Shuri to come with her, but she informed her of other business she had deal with.{{Ref|BPWF}}

