==Powers and Abilities==
===Powers=== 
*'''Ironheart Armor Capabilities''': Williams uses a set of [[:Category:Ironheart Armors|technologically advanced armors]] which provides her of the ability to flight and grant her superhuman strength, durability, speed, agility, stamina and reflexes. The armors also possess energy repulsors and other offensive weapons.
**'''Superhuman Strength''': With her armors, Williams can enhance her strength to superhuman levels, enough to defeat [[Talokanil]] [[Talokanil Armed Forces|soldiers]] and [[Namora]].
**'''Superhuman Durability''': With her armors, Williams can withstand tremendous amounts of punishment. Her first armor was durable enough to withstand bullets and brute force, and most impressively, a fall from 30,000 feet (over five miles). Her second armor made of [[vibranium]] was incredibly durable against Namora's weapons.
**'''Superhuman Speed''': With her armors, the thrusters grants Riri to move as super fast distances with supports of the repulsors.
**'''Superhuman Agility''': With her armors, despite the heavy metal is incredibly agile to allow Williams to perform evasive movements.
** '''Superhuman Stamina''': ''To be added''
**'''Superhuman Reflexes''': ''To be added''
**[[File:BP Wakanda Forever Trailer (46).png|thumb|250px|Ironheart enables her thrusters]]'''Flight''': Riri's armor has the innate ability of flight, capable of soaring through the air and even high altitudes to reach near outer space.
**'''Power Suit''': Using designs of Stark blueprints, Williams came up with a sustainable arc reactor to power all her own suit’s operating functions to successfully remain active.

===Abilities===
{{Quote|This thing can detect the altered frequency of [[vibranium]] through water, stones, even heavy metals. Whoever built this is brilliant. Come, look. Some are custom parts and others look like they gathered it from a junkyard.|[[Black Panther|Shuri]]|Black Panther: Wakanda Forever}}
*'''Genius-Level Intellect''': Williams is a child prodigy who attends the prestigious [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]] and had been "running circles around" all of her professors according to [[Everett Ross]]. She was referred to as "brilliant" by [[Shuri]]; given that the latter is the smartest person in the world,<ref>[https://www.cbr.com/black-panther-shuri-smartest-person/ Black Panther's Sister Shuri Is 'the Smartest Person in the World']</ref> this is high praise.
*[[File:BP Wakanda Forever Trailer (44).png|thumb|250px|Riri creates a new [[Ironheart Armor: Mark II|Ironheart armor]]]]'''Master Engineer''': Williams was three years old when she built her first machine, with encouragement from her stepfather. She built the [[vibranium]] detector for her metallurgy class in the span of a couple months using custom parts and others gathered from a junkyard. According to Doctor [[Graham (Doctor)|Graham]], the machine had less than a one in a billion chance of finding the substance, but it worked. [[Shuri]] learned that it could detect the altered frequency of vibranium through water, stones, and even heavy metals. She also corrected the grip algorithm of one of her coed's robotic hands in exchange for payment, and fixed a few trucks for the head of sanitation. She built a functional quantum computer to crack her own encryption.
*'''Master Scientist''': Williams' differential equations class allowed her to find Euler angles while flying her [[Ironheart Armor: Mark I|suit]] and take down a federal surveillance drone. Still, it is very dependent on its own scientific field, in this case engineering, which prevented it from advancing in the research of the [[Hood's Cloak]].
*'''Master Hacker''': Williams impressed [[Shuri]] with the 2065-byte encryption on her laptop and had to build a functional quantum computer to crack it when she was locked out.
*'''Combatant''': ''To be added''
*'''Marksman''': ''To be added''
*'''Expert Pilot''': ''To be added''

==Equipment==
===Ironheart Armors===
{{Quote|Oh, shit! She got a [[Iron Man]] [[Ironheart Armor: Mark I|suit]]!|FBI Officer|Black Panther: Wakanda Forever}}
*'''[[Ironheart Armor: Mark I]]''': Williams uses blueprints from Stark technology to craft her own design of Iron Man armor, where Mark I can shoot repulsors and fly powered through an arc reactor shaped like a heart.
*'''[[Ironheart Armor: Mark II]]''': With aid of the Wakandan technology Riri designs a second model of Ironheart suit completely of vibranium, heads up display, including better weaponry more advanced than the suit that it can even travel underwater.
*'''[[Ironheart Armor: Mark III]]''': Using her grant money as a student at MIT, she developed the third iteration of Ironheart Armor, which was less weapons capable due to it's prototyped nature. It also featured a heads up display, and supersonic flight capabilities, and a basic life support system.
*'''[[Ironheart Armor: Mark IV]]''': Recollecting the pieces of her broken Mark lll, she uses replacement parts to reassemble her Mark lV suit to install [[N.A.T.A.L.I.E.]] as new A.I program to operate it for missions stealing from high-tech corporations.
*'''[[Ironheart Armor: Mark V]]''': With help from family and peers Riri took parts of her stepdad‘s old car that was refurbished with Wankandan technology to craft armor Mark V with the exception of mixing it with [[magic]].

===Other Equipment===
*'''[[Vibranium Detector]]''': As a project for school, Williams crafted a device capable of detecting minerals underwater so powerful that it can even detect vibranium, thus why the CIA used it for operations.
*'''Projection Necklace''': To get her AI assistant ([[N.A.T.A.L.I.E.]]) to cooperate, Williams developed a device capable of projecting a holographic avatar of [[N.A.T.A.L.I.E.]], which can be worn as a necklace to do so in public without rousing suspicion.
*'''[[Bio-Mesh Skin]]''': ''To be Added''

==Facilities==
*'''[[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]]''': Williams is a student at MIT known to use her education and dedication to her role of being a gifted inventor.
*'''[[Riri Williams' Garage]]''': On her private time really owns the garage near campus where she hold all her personal projects, including her own Ironheart armors.
*'''[[Shuri's Lab]]''': Assigned by Shuri, Williams was provided a work station to help build defenses against Namor while at the same time building her first advanced version Ironheart suit.
*'''[[Citadel]]''': Under protective custody of Wakanda, Riri was escorted by Queen Ramonda in the Citadel during the attack by the [[Talokanil]].

