==Trivia==
*In the comics, Riri Williams is a young [[MIT]] student who managed to reverse-engineer [[Iron Man]] technology and create her own suit of armor, becoming known as Ironheart. She was approached by Tony Stark himself who endorsed her desire to be a superhero, so she joined him in the second Civil War against [[Captain Marvel]].
*Williams is a fan of {{WPS|Chicago Bulls}}, [[Alanis Morissette]] and ''{{WPS|Star Trek}}''.

==Behind the Scenes==
*[[Dominique Thorne]] was called up by [[Marvel Studios]] and asked if she wanted to play Ironheart instead of submitting an audition as usual: "''I was at home in Delaware and I got a call asking if I would like to play this role. It was the best phone call I could have ever received. I was so shocked, in fact, that there was a considerable lag in the conversation! I was waiting for them to say, like, ‘Oh, we’ll send you the sides’, or, ‘Get your tape over to us.’ But there was none of that. It was just like, ‘Would you like to do this?’ It was probably the most unique experience I’ve ever had because there was no audition at all''".<ref>[https://www.empireonline.com/movies/news/marvel-ironheart-dominique-thorne-cast-riri-williams-no-audition-exclusive/ Marvel’s Ironheart Star Dominique Thorne On Being Cast As Riri Williams With ‘No Audition At All’ – Exclusive]</ref> 
*Thorne originally auditioned to play [[Shuri]] in the first ''[[Black Panther (film)|Black Panther]]'' back when she was still in her sophomore year. While she didn't get the role, Thorne later starred in a film produced by director [[Ryan Coogler]], ''{{WPS|Judas and the Black Messiah}}'', leading executive producer [[Nate Moore]] to call her, asking her if she was familiar with the Ironheart character and then offer it to her when she affirmed that she did know about the character.<ref>[https://ew.com/movies/black-panther-wakanda-forever-cover-story/ ''Forever'' changed: The grief and joy of ''Black Panther: Wakanda Forever'']</ref>
*[[Kellina Rutherford]], [[Diandra Stoddard]] and [[Alex Patrice Lapeyrolerie]] were stunt doubles for [[Dominique Thorne]] in the role of Ironheart.

